Deuterogeny of
Phytoptus hirtae
.
Protogyne and deutogyne females of P. h i r t a e ( 10 of each from samples # 9 & # 10 ;
Table 2
) collected in the same meadow near the village of Gogolevo, Russia , were measured and compared to reveal the existence of deuterogeny. Generally, summer and overwintered females are identical except for differences in the length of setae: overwintered females have longer setae ve, e, f and shorter coxal setae
1 b
(
Table 4
). Moreover, in comparison to uncoloured, whitish summer females, overwintering females are yellowish.

